#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.86"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.86:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.86:0.2"
msgid "9. Samaṇavagga"
msgstr "9. Ascetics"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.86:0.3"
msgid "86. Paṭhamasikkhāsutta"
msgstr "86. Training (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.86:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Sādhikamidaṃ, bhikkhave, diyaḍḍhasikkhāpadasataṃ anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ "
"āgacchati, yattha attakāmā kulaputtā sikkhanti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, each fortnight over a hundred and fifty training rules come up "
"for recitation, in which respectable people who love themselves train."

msgctxt "an3.86:1.2"
msgid "Tisso imā, bhikkhave, sikkhā yatthetaṃ sabbaṃ samodhānaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "These are all included in the three trainings."

msgctxt "an3.86:1.3"
msgid "Katamā tisso?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.86:1.4"
msgid "Adhisīlasikkhā, adhicittasikkhā adhipaññāsikkhā—"
msgstr ""
"The training in the higher ethics, the higher mind, and the higher wisdom."

msgctxt "an3.86:1.5"
msgid "imā kho, bhikkhave, tisso sikkhā, yatthetaṃ sabbaṃ samodhānaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "These are the three trainings that include them all."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.232"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.86:2.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti samādhismiṃ mattaso kārī "
"paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Take the case of a mendicant who has fulfilled their ethics, but has limited "
"immersion and wisdom."

msgctxt "an3.86:2.2"
msgid ""
"So yāni tāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni tāni āpajjatipi vuṭṭhātipi."
msgstr "They break some lesser and minor training rules, but are restored."

msgctxt "an3.86:2.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.86:2.4"
msgid "Na hi mettha, bhikkhave, abhabbatā vuttā."
msgstr "Because I don’t say they’re not capable."

#. VAR: dhuvasīlo → dhuvasīlī (bj)
#. VAR: ṭhitasīlo → ṭhitasīlī (bj)
msgctxt "an3.86:2.5"
msgid ""
"Yāni ca kho tāni sikkhāpadāni ādibrahmacariyakāni brahmacariyasāruppāni, "
"tattha dhuvasīlo ca hoti ṭhitasīlo ca, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"But they’re constant and steady in their precepts regarding the training "
"rules that are fundamental, appropriate for the spiritual path. They keep "
"the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an3.86:2.6"
msgid ""
"So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā sotāpanno hoti avinipātadhammo niyato "
"sambodhiparāyaṇo."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of three fetters they’re a stream-enterer, not liable to be "
"reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.86:3.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti samādhismiṃ mattaso "
"kārī paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Take another case of a mendicant who has fulfilled their ethics, but has "
"limited immersion and wisdom."

msgctxt "an3.86:3.2"
msgid ""
"So yāni tāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni tāni āpajjatipi vuṭṭhātipi."
msgstr "They break some lesser and minor training rules, but are restored."

msgctxt "an3.86:3.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.86:3.4"
msgid "Na hi mettha, bhikkhave, abhabbatā vuttā."
msgstr "Because I don’t say they’re not capable."

msgctxt "an3.86:3.5"
msgid ""
"Yāni ca kho tāni sikkhāpadāni ādibrahmacariyakāni brahmacariyasāruppāni "
"tattha dhuvasīlo ca hoti ṭhitasīlo ca, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"But they’re constant and steady in their precepts regarding the training "
"rules that are fundamental, appropriate for the spiritual path. They keep "
"the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an3.86:3.6"
msgid ""
"So tiṇṇaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā rāgadosamohānaṃ tanuttā sakadāgāmī hoti, "
"sakideva imaṃ lokaṃ āgantvā dukkhassantaṃ karoti."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of three fetters, and the weakening of greed, hate, and "
"delusion, they’re a once-returner. They come back to this world once only, "
"then make an end of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.86:4.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti samādhismiṃ "
"paripūrakārī paññāya mattaso kārī."
msgstr ""
"Take another case of a mendicant who has fulfilled their ethics and "
"immersion, but has limited wisdom."

msgctxt "an3.86:4.2"
msgid ""
"So yāni tāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni tāni āpajjatipi vuṭṭhātipi."
msgstr "They break some lesser and minor training rules, but are restored."

msgctxt "an3.86:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.86:4.4"
msgid "Na hi mettha, bhikkhave, abhabbatā vuttā."
msgstr "Because I don’t say they’re incapable."

msgctxt "an3.86:4.5"
msgid ""
"Yāni ca kho tāni sikkhāpadāni ādibrahmacariyakāni brahmacariyasāruppāni "
"tattha dhuvasīlo ca hoti ṭhitasīlo ca, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"But they’re constant and steady in their precepts regarding the training "
"rules that are fundamentals, appropriate for the spiritual path. They keep "
"the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an3.86:4.6"
msgid ""
"So pañcannaṃ orambhāgiyānaṃ saṃyojanānaṃ parikkhayā opapātiko hoti tattha "
"parinibbāyī anāvattidhammo tasmā lokā."
msgstr ""
"With the ending of the five lower fetters they’re reborn spontaneously. They "
"are extinguished there, and are not liable to return from that world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.86:5.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlesu paripūrakārī hoti samādhismiṃ "
"paripūrakārī paññāya paripūrakārī."
msgstr ""
"Take another case of a mendicant who has fulfilled their ethics, immersion, "
"and wisdom."

msgctxt "an3.86:5.2"
msgid ""
"So yāni tāni khuddānukhuddakāni sikkhāpadāni tāni āpajjatipi vuṭṭhātipi."
msgstr "They break some lesser and minor training rules, but are restored."

msgctxt "an3.86:5.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "an3.86:5.4"
msgid "Na hi mettha, bhikkhave, abhabbatā vuttā."
msgstr "Because I don’t say they’re not capable."

msgctxt "an3.86:5.5"
msgid ""
"Yāni ca kho tāni sikkhāpadāni ādibrahmacariyakāni brahmacariyasāruppāni "
"tattha dhuvasīlo ca hoti ṭhitasīlo ca, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu."
msgstr ""
"But they’re constant and steady in their precepts regarding the training "
"rules that are fundamental, appropriate for the spiritual path. They keep "
"the rules they’ve undertaken."

msgctxt "an3.86:5.6"
msgid ""
"So āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati."
msgstr ""
"They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this "
"very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.86:6.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, padesaṃ padesakārī ārādheti paripūraṃ paripūrakārī."
msgstr ""
"So, mendicants, if you practice partially you succeed partially. If you "
"practice fully you succeed fully."

#. VAR: Avañjhāni tvevāhaṃ → avañjhānevāhaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.86:6.2"
msgid "Avañjhāni tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sikkhāpadāni vadāmī”ti."
msgstr "These training rules are not a waste, I say.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.86:6.3"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
